dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is more challenging than CIFAR-10 and is used for evaluating image classification algorithms.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:description: A dataset that is a smaller version of ImageNet, containing 200 classes with 500 training images and 50 test images per class. It is used for benchmarking image classification models.
dcterms:title: Tiny-ImageNet
